race.comment: KAWASAKI GIRL (2) is in top form, scoring by 4 lengths (17.57) over 300m at this track and making it back to back wins. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from three starts. Looks to have an edge on most of these. TOMMIE'S BRIDE (7) goes very well this course and distance starting eight times for three wins and four minors. In the money last time at this track (17.66) in a Grade 5, finishing a 2.75 lengths third. Looks a key chance on best figures. MADAWASKA (1) has missed the frame at her last two but did run well three back when second (17.63) in a Grade 5 at this track. Can hit the frame this time. SEMTEX (3) is a last start winner who can measure up again.
